        <h2 id="faq" class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-950">FAQ</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600">To address common questions and misconceptions about trust-building case studies, this section provides clear, concise answers tailored to Manchester-based sales teams.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600">**Q: How long should a trust-building case study be?** A: The ideal length for a trust-building case study is between 500 and 1,500 words. This range allows for sufficient detail while maintaining reader engagement.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600">**Q: Should I use visuals in my trust-building case studies?** A: Absolutely! Incorporating relevant images, charts, and graphs enhances the visual appeal of case studies and helps readers understand complex information more easily.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600">**Q: How often should I update my trust-building case studies?** A: Regularly review and update your case studies to ensure they remain relevant and accurate. Aim to refresh your portfolio every 6 to 12 months, or whenever significant changes occur in your product, service, or target market.</p>
      </section>
